text=>>recipeinfo%3c%3c%0a(:linebreaks:)%0aSummary: a skin implementing Twitter Bootstrap formattin, using wiki pages to define page elements%0aVersion: 2013-06-16%0aPrerequisites: pmwiki-2.x%0aStatus: new%0aMaintainer: [[http://www.pmwiki.org/wiki/Profiles/Tamouse|tamouse]] %0aCategories: [[!Skins]]%0aUsers: {$Users} ([[{$FullName}-Users|view]] / [[{$FullName}-Users?action=edit|edit]])%0aDiscussion: [[{$Name}-Talk]]%0a(:nolinebreaks:)%0a>>%3c%3c%0a[[#desc]]%0a!! Description%0a(:Description {$:Summary}:){$Description}%0a%0a[[#install]]%0a!! Installation%0a%0a# Download Attach:bootstrap-skin.zip  to some place safe.%0a%0a# Go to your wiki's pub/skins directory and Unzip the skin package:[@%0a%0a  $ cd path/to/wiki/pub/skins%0a  $ unzip path/to/where/you/saved/bootstrap-skin.zip%0a@]%0a%0a# Alternatively, get a clone of the git repository at [@git://github.com/tamouse/pmwiki-bootstrap-skin.git@]:[@%0a%0a  $ cd path/to/wiki/pub/skins%0a  $ git clone git://github.com/tamouse/pmwiki-bootstrap-skin.git bootstrap-skin%0a@]%0a%0a[[#config]]%0a!! Configuration%0a%0aAdd [@$Skin='bootstrap-skin';@] to your ''local/config.php'' file to use this skin.%0a%0a[[#layout]]%0a!! Layout%0a%0aBootstrapSkin makes use of the lovely [[http://twitter.github.io/bootstrap|Twitter Bootstrap]] style framework.%0a%0a[[#usage]]%0a!! Usage%0a%0aBootstrapSkin uses the contents of various wiki pages in order to define page elements in the layout. Defaults for the above pages are included in the skin's wikilib.d directory (automatically bundled in the wiki page store).%0a%0a%25p class=alert%25 In the standard installation, only the default page is included, because they use bootstrap styles. You can edit the page to include other page elements if you wish, but refer to the default page to find out the bootstrap styles needed.%0a%0a* [@%3c!--PageLeftFmt-->@] includes the [=BootstrapSkin-SideBar=] page. Defaults are in [=Site.BootstrapSkin-DefaultSideBar=]%0a* [@%3c!--PageActionsFmt-->@] includes the [=BootstrapSkin-PageActions=] page. Defaults are in [=Site.BootstrapSkin-DefaultPageActions=]%0a* [@%3c!--PageHeaderFmt-->@] includes the [=BootstrapSkin-SiteHeader=] page. This contains just the top nav bar navigation links, not the logo, title, or search form. Defaults are in [=Site.BootstrapSkin-DefaultSiteHeader=]%0a* [@%3c!--PageTitleFmt-->@] includes the [=BootstrapSkin-PageTitle=] page. This goes at the top of every wiki page. Defaults are in [=Site.BootstrapSkin-DefaultPageTitle=]%0a* [@%3c!--PageFooterFmt-->@] includes the [=BootstrapSkin-SiteFooter=] page. This goes at the bottom of the site. Defaults are in [=Site.BootstrapSkin-DefaultPageFooter=]%0a%0a%0a[[#notes]]%0a!! Notes%0a%0a# When editing or navigating to a page that does not exist, the page actions end up as a double line due to the way the extra ? is added to new links. I've overridden the style in bootstrap.css to set these to display:none.%0a%0a# The template pulls in [[jQuery -> http://jquery.com/]], so if you have recipes that also use jQuery, make sure they don't conflict.%0a%0a# jQuery and Bootstrap are pulled from CDNs:%0a** jQuery: http://code.jquery.com/%0a** Bootstrap: http://www.bootstrapcdn.com/%0a%0a[[#relnotes]]%0a!! Change log / Release notes%0a* 2013-06-16: Initial release.%0a%0a%25comment%25 If the recipe has multiple releases, then release notes can be placed here. Note that it's often easier for people to work with "release dates" instead of "version numbers".%0a%0a[[#seealso]]%0a!! See also%0a%0a%0a[[#contributors]]%0a!! Contributors%0a* [[http://www.pmwiki.org/wiki/Profiles/Tamouse|tamouse]]%0a%0a[[#comments]]%0a!! Comments%0aSee discussion at [[{$Name}-Talk]]%0a%0a[[#faq]]%0a>>faq display=none%3c%3c%0a%0aQ:%0aA:%0a